---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import { HOME } from "@consts";
---

<PageLayout title={HOME.TITLE} description={HOME.DESCRIPTION}>
  <div class="pt-8 md:pt-20 max-w-2xl">

    <section class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-10 items-start mb-20">
      <img
        src="/headshot.jpg"
        alt="Adam Byrne"
        class="w-24 h-24 object-cover grayscale shrink-0"
      />
      <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Hi, I'm Adam. I write systems software: databases, kernels, simulators.
          I studied through <a target="_blank" href="https://software-engineering.ie">ISE (MSc)</a>, a residency-based programme where half the degree is spent in industry.
          My placements covered factory automation and teleoperation, ADAS radar ML, and AI investment research.
          Alongside that I worked on simulation and payload software for high-powered competition rockets.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-1">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold">Apogee</h2>
        <span class="text-sm text-paper-muted">
          <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/bxrne/apogee" class="underline underline-offset-2">github</a>
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-paper-muted mb-6">A minimal x86-64 bare-metal kernel in Rust exploring deterministic parallelism.</p>

      <div class="space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
	  Apogee runs on bare metal with no underlying OS, implementing paging, heap allocation, cooperative kernel threads, and async task execution. The goal is deterministic parallelism: given the same input seed, execution produces the same trace every time. It features lock-free scheduler observability, a ring-3 demo user-mode process with syscalls, and a deterministic PRNG as the foundation for reproducible execution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-1">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold">Tau</h2>
        <span class="text-sm text-paper-muted">
          <a target="_blank" href="https://tau.bxrne.com" class="underline underline-offset-2">tau.bxrne.com</a>
          <span class="mx-1">·</span>
          <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/bxrne/tau" class="underline underline-offset-2">github</a>
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-paper-muted mb-6">A bitemporal time-series database where corrections are appended as new layers, not edits.</p>

      <div class="space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
	  Tau stores data as half-open intervals with valid time and transaction time, treating every correction as a new layer rather than an edit. It ships a small query language (TauQL) for defining raw layers, derived series, and materialised views that refresh themselves when their sources are corrected. The result is a time-series-native materialized view system where compaction normalizes the layer stack without losing auditability.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm">
          <Link href="/blog/15-tau">Read the full writeup →</Link>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold mb-4">Elsewhere</h2>
      <p class="text-paper-muted leading-relaxed">
        <Link href="https://github.com/bxrne" external>GitHub</Link> ·
        <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bxrne" external>LinkedIn</Link> ·
        <Link href="https://twitter.com/abxrne" external>Twitter</Link> ·
        <Link href="https://substack.com/@bxrne" external>Substack</Link> ·
        <Link href="/resume.pdf" external>CV</Link>
      </p>
    </section>

  </div>
</PageLayout>
